                <note rend="inline" type="source">890g.6363 T 84/257: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-06T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1926—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 6—1:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Am informed by Teagle of the Standard Oil that Gulbenkian has agreed to a
                    basis of settlement in the Turkish Petroleum matter which is satisfactory to the
                    two English groups as well as to the American Group. The details of the
                    settlement have been forwarded to French Group for approval. Teagle is hopeful
                    for a final and favorable conclusion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
